WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: IVM.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.660
[Amit Varma]: Unity unites us and we can celebrate together in different ways.

00:01:03.660 --> 00:01:07.480
[Amit Varma]: But politics in Maharashtra is based more around what divides us.

00:01:07.480 --> 00:01:10.340
[Amit Varma]: Do you speak Marathi or Gujarati or Hindi?

00:01:10.340 --> 00:01:12.460
[Amit Varma]: Are you Brahmin or Maratha or Dalit?

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:15.580
[Amit Varma]: Are you from Vidarbha or Marathwada or Konkan or Mumbai?

00:01:15.580 --> 00:01:17.240
[Amit Varma]: Are you a farmer or a banker?

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:23.280
[Amit Varma]: And amid these divisions, there is one overarching quality that unites all political parties.

00:01:23.280 --> 00:01:26.120
[Amit Varma]: Opportunism, the will to power.

00:01:26.120 --> 00:01:30.640
[Amit Varma]: That's the central theme that runs through the gripping ongoing drama of Maharashtra

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:31.640
[Amit Varma]: politics.

00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:41.080
[Unknown]: Welcome to the scene and the unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioral

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:42.080
[Unknown]: science.

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:45.080
[Unknown]: Please welcome your host, Amit Verma.

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:48.520
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the scene and the unseen.

00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:52.400
[Amit Varma]: Maharashtra politics has been in the news recently, but in this episode, I want to take

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:56.000
[Amit Varma]: a broader and deeper look at it than what we get in the present.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.280
[Amit Varma]: I want to take a journey through the last few decades of Maharashtra politics and try

00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:04.360
[Amit Varma]: to get a better grip on this deeply complex ecosystem.

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:08.600
[Amit Varma]: And I cannot think of a better guest for this purpose than Sujata Anandan.

00:02:08.600 --> 00:02:13.400
[Amit Varma]: Sujata has been a political reporter since the 1980s, and I've been admiring her columns

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:17.880
[Amit Varma]: on local politics since I first came to Mumbai in 1995.

00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:23.160
[Amit Varma]: She's also written two deeply insightful books, Hindu Hriday Samrat about the life and times

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:28.280
[Amit Varma]: of Balasaheb Thackeray and the Shiv Sena and Maharashtra Maximus, a broader sociopolitical

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:30.000
[Amit Varma]: history of the state.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.200
[Amit Varma]: She's a legend in the space, and I'm delighted that she's agreed to come on the show and

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:36.160
[Amit Varma]: share her insights with me.

